138
00:08:40,659 --> 00:08:41,260
Of course.

139
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:43,350
Captain Cheng is definitely the best

140
00:08:43,350 --> 00:08:44,880
in the Freight Department.

141
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,550
Just see how I'll deal with him later.

142
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:50,920
Next two candidates, Cheng Xiao and Song Song.

143
00:08:53,230 --> 00:08:53,690
Come on!

144
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:54,380
Come on!

145
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,020
Let's wait and see.

146
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,310
Hello, leaders.

147
00:09:05,310 --> 00:09:06,240
Hello, leaders.

148
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:19,160
Sit down.

149
00:09:26,380 --> 00:09:26,830
Mr. Gu.

150
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:28,740
This is my resume.

151
00:09:29,410 --> 00:09:30,470
Please have a look.

152
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:32,580
If you have any questions,

153
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:33,380
please ask me.

154
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:49,810
Cheng Xiao, right?

155
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:53,000
Don't be so serious.

156
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,330
We're just chatting.

157
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:56,580
Have a seat.

158
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:02,080
Mr. Gu,

159
00:10:03,410 --> 00:10:04,940
she mentioned you just now.

160
00:10:05,210 --> 00:10:06,870
You should ask her questions.

161
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,830
Why did you choose

162
00:10:12,100 --> 00:10:13,120
the career as a pilot?

163
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,250
Because of freedom.

164
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:19,160
Flying can make us get rid of gravity.

165
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:22,090
I can be so free on the surface of the Earth,

166
00:10:22,230 --> 00:10:25,150
and sit in an office where I can see the most beautiful sceneries in the world,

167
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:27,550
chasing the sun and having stars' company.

168
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,040
Of course,

169
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,410
there is another important and pracitcal reason.

170
00:10:31,410 --> 00:10:32,470
The income is high.

171
00:10:33,940 --> 00:10:36,150
The career as a pilot can give me economic freedom

172
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:37,680
so that I can follow my heart

173
00:10:37,730 --> 00:10:38,930
and live more freely.

174
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:39,780
So,

175
00:10:40,830 --> 00:10:43,490
this is your attitude with which you fly a plane?

176
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,920
Flight work is about rules and discipline.

177
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,180
You have to pay the price of freedom

178
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:49,380
to fulfill your duty.

179
00:10:49,590 --> 00:10:51,520
Do you know how serious this job is?

180
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,230
I joined this company in 2013.

181
00:10:55,230 --> 00:10:57,130
My flight time is up to 3,500 hours.

182
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:59,680
My flight experience time is as long as 2,700 hours.

183
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:01,080
There is no error record.

184
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,360
All the evaluations have been passed excellently.

185
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,120
Besides,

186
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:06,140
I also have the certificate of Aviation English Level Five,

187
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:08,790
and the qualification of English communication for international flights.

188
00:11:08,790 --> 00:11:11,430
This is my answer to serious work.

189
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:14,820
[Xie Zetian, Luzhou Airlines]

190
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:14,820
[Director of the Security Department of Luzhou Airlines]

191
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,600
For your recent performance,

192
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:18,720
you landed at the extreme wind speed.

193
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:20,080
No matter how stable the landing was,

194
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,600
there should be a comment on it.

195
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,490
The weather was so bad that day.

196
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:24,960
With my good skills, I managed to

197
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,300
land the plane safely.

198
00:11:26,530 --> 00:11:27,590
Is there a problem?

199
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,370
Did we have to divert the plane to land it elsewhere,

200
00:11:29,370 --> 00:11:30,850
and make the company lose hundreds of thousands of yuan?

201
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:32,990
Flight safety is not measured by money.

202
00:11:32,990 --> 00:11:33,990
I'll say it again.

203
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:36,600
There wasn't any problem with my landing operation.

204
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,450
Nor did I violate

205
00:11:37,450 --> 00:11:39,420
the current flight safety manual.

206
00:11:43,410 --> 00:11:45,510
Since you're in the Passenger Transport Department,

207
00:11:45,510 --> 00:11:47,170
let's wait till the interview is finished,

208
00:11:47,170 --> 00:11:49,340
and then have further communication about

209
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:51,060
the landing operation on that day.

